FAQ-GEN-Q01
%%
General Information
%%
MiniVend is a freely-redistributable electronic catalog, otherwise known as a
shopping cart.  It serves a catalog via the World Wide Web, allowing
users to select items for placement on their shopping list, or cart, and
then buy them by filling out an order form.  Since MiniVend supports
Secure Sockets Layer (SSL), the customer can securely put their credit
card number in the form if you have an HTTP server that supports SSL.

MiniVend supports a host of features -- a complete list is available at
its web home page:


<PRE>
        <A HREF="http://www.iac.net/~mikeh/mvend.html">http://www.iac.net/~mikeh/mvend.html</A>

</PRE>

MiniVend is written and maintained by Mike Heins, but more than
half of the credit goes to Andrew Wilcox, who originated Vend and
created most of the underlying algorithms.

MiniVend is freely redistributable under the GNU General Public License,
a copy of which should come with every MiniVend package. Basically
this means that you can use it for commercial or non-commercial
purposes for free, but you you have certain responsibilities if you
modify and/or redistribute it. See the GNU GPL for more information.


