%%%
FAQ-GEN-Q04
%%
If you are intending to run MiniVend on an ISP
%%
Many Internet Service Provider (ISP) systems have difficulty with
one or the other aspect of running MiniVend.  A few cannot (or will
not) run MiniVend at all.  On top of that, many times ISP personnel are
too busy to help, won't help, or don't know enough to help.  Some are
secretive about details of the setup of their systems.  And some
systems are so overtaxed that MiniVend (especially in static mode)
performs poorly.

In short, be forewarned.  Don't expect a trouble-free installation on an
ISP. A list of some of the [page scan/se=ISP/mp=1]common
problems seen with ISPs[/page] is included in this FAQ.


